               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Oriental paper</support>
                        <extent>322 folios (i+322+i)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>169</height>
                              <width>125</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>128</height>
                              <width>83</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliation in Arabic numerals.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>Indeterminable (binding too tight).</p>
                           <p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>Usage stains, smudged ink.</p>
                           <p>Water damage.</p>
                           <p>Some leaves have been reinforced.</p>
                           <p>Fol. 1 is fragmentary.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
                           <p>Ruling (with mastara?) is visible.</p>
                           <p>Fols. 2v-23r: running title added by a later hand.</p>
                           <p>A few marginal notes.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <summary>Oriental (Persian) square script of the 15th century.</summary>
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole" />
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote />
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Hebrew note on fol. 322r.</p>
                     <p>Fol. 322v: Poem in Hebrew added by a different hand.</p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <p>BM in-house, half-bound.</p>
                        <p>Spine: 'Pentateuch &amp; Haphṭaroth. Hebrew &amp; Persian. Brit. Mus. Oriental
                  9884.'</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <accMat>
                     <p>Fols. 1-7: Gen. 1:1-1:11: later addition, different kind of paper (with laid and
                chain lines, traces of watermark), later hand.</p>
                     <p>Small paper slip is fixed into the leaf encapsulating the fragment of fol. 1. On
                the paper slip French description of the MS.</p>
                  </accMat>
               </physDesc>
